  "texts": [
    "The COVID-19 dataset 2 (as described in Sect. 3) consists of 835 instances of fake classes and 702 instances of nonfake classes.",
    "Tables 6 and 7 illustrate the statistics of the original dataset and the augmented dataset.",
    "The data augmentation (DA) process results in an increase in the amount of training data for both fake and non-fake classes.",
    "Since the back-translation DA technique provides diversity and novelty to the generated data instances, the unique words in the augmented dataset have increased by 1552 for the fake class and 1490 for the non-fake class compared to the original dataset.",
    "Additionally, the number of new instances has increased by 449 for the fake class and 379 for the nonfake class."
